					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I realize that your adorable pythons may not follow the same rules of coding us humans do, but I feel obligated to point out that their code doesn't always follow computer logic. For instance, the lines:</p> <p>snake=snek<br /> snek=super cute</p> <p>should have their order swapped. The assignment of 'super cute' to 'snek' should be made before assigning 'snek' to 'snake' if their goal is to become super cute.</p> <p>But who am I to question reality-bending snakes. You still get a +1 from me</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
