					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12981657#post-4481799</guid>
				<title>Well done!</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12981657/scp-3529#post-4481799</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 28 Jan 2020 15:10:06 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>BoomerTheStar47_2</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5567329</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Only familiar with javascript, so&#8230;</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>function read (reader.Name, reader.Like)={<br /> interest++<br /> if reader.Like = &quot;positive&quot;<br /> reader.Rating = 1<br /> rating++<br /> elif reader.Like = &quot;negative&quot;<br /> reader.Rating = -1<br /> rating&#8212;<br /> elif reader.Like = &quot;neutral&quot;<br /> reader.Rating = 0<br /> end<br /> print(reader.Name + &quot; has left a &quot; + reader.Rating + &quot; rating.&quot;)<br /> }<br /> read(BoomerTheStar47_2, positive);</p> <p>&quot;BoomerTheStar47_2 has left a +1 rating.&quot;</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>Only change I would recommend is that the Foundation do something to prevent SCP-3529 instances occurring in containment so that another breach doesn't happen. Other than that, this article is perfect! +1 indeed!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
